<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=Martin_Amis&amp;action=edit&amp;section=14" title="Edit section: Sample works and articles by Amis">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Sample works and articles by Amis</span></h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,2099-1458940,00.html" class="external text" title="http://www.timesonline.co.uk/article/0,,2099-1458940,00.html" rel="nofollow">Authors in the front line</a>: Martin Amis, The Sunday Times Magazine, 6 February 2005 – On the streets of Colombia, young boys cripple or murder each other just for showing disrespect or for winning at a game of cards. Is the taste for violence opening up a wound that can never heal? Report: Martin Amis – In The Sunday Times Magazine's continuing series of articles, renowned writers bring a fresh perspective to the world's trouble spots. The international medical-aid organisation <a href="/wiki/MSF" title="MSF">MSF</a> has helped our correspondents reach some of these inhospitable areas.</li>
<li><a href="http://www.randomhouse.com/boldtype/0299/amis/sstory1.html" class="external text" title="http://www.randomhouse.com/boldtype/0299/amis/sstory1.html" rel="nofollow"><i>CareerMove</i></a> - A complete short story by Amis.</li>
